an air force a10a thunderbolt ii attack plane 
crashed in woods in western louisiana durinng a combat training 
mission thursday killing the pilot england air force base 
officials said 
the plane went down around 130 pm in rural sabine parish 
between the towns of negreet and florien state police said 
the pilot was identified as 1st lt michael n ayotte 24 of 
bexar county texas ayotte was attached to the 75th tactical 
fighter squadron of the 23rd tactical fighter wing at the central 
louisiana air base an air force news release said 
the cause of the crash was not immediately known the air force 
said the crash would be investigated 
