task forces and special offices they want us to have wed probably 
have to go out and buy another building as big as the two we have 
now 
the brown amendment which now goes before the full house 
agriculture committee said that the composting of agricultural 
wastes can help prevent contamination of water supplies and 
alleviate waste removal burdens on farmers 
further it said compost can be a safe and useful soil 
additive which can help to stabilize and enrich the soil and 
reduce the use of chemical fertilizers 
the department of agriculture is uniquely qualified to 
research appropriate uses and markets for compost the proposal 
said 
