two out of three defendants charged with 
felonies in 39 of the nations largest counties were released from 
police custody pending court action says a justice department 
study 
the sampling released thursday of 11063 felony cases filed in 
february 1988 showed that 66 percent of the defendants were freed 
on bail bond or their own recognizance while awaiting trial or the 
dispositions of their cases 
thirtyone percent were held in jail pending trial because they 
were unable to post bail and 4 percent were ordered held without 
bail following their arraignments the study said 
the statistics gathered from local courts by the justice 
departments bureau of justice statistics were intended to be a 
sampling of the disposition of felony charges in 75 of the nations 
largest counties 
