while in a car after the democratic state convention in austin 
ive never used any marijuana or dangerous drugs period 
mattox said about the accusations which sharp and lowe made in the 
houston chronicle and the dallas morning news 
the incidents the two men described absolutely did not take 
place mattox said today 
ive never been in a car where there has ever been any 
marijuana smoked by me or anybody else mattox said 
the drug use issue first was presented at a debate before the 
march 13 primary mattox and former gov mark white denied ever 
using illegal drugs but ms richards the state treasurer refused 
to answer the question 
ms richards a recovering alcoholic later said she has not had 
an alcoholic drink or a moodaltering chemical since leaving an 
alcohol recovery program in 1980 
the issue has dominated the democratic campaign particularly 
since the primary that vaulted mattox and ms richards into the 
runoff mattox has said a former drug user could not effectively 
lead the states efforts to end illegal drug use 
ms richards has not accused mattox of drug use 
earlier this week mattox said he had affidavits signed by 
people who saw ms richards use drugs in the 1970s but he has 
refused to release the documents citing the confidentiality of the 
people who made the allegations 
on thursday the houston post quoted a woman it didnt identify 
