<TEXT>
thai fishermen armed with knives 
and iron rods attacked a boat carrying 191 refugees from vietnam 
stabbing to death three refugees and kidnapping six of the women 
un officials said friday 
eleven other refugees were missing and presumed drowned said 
the un high commissioner for refugees 
it was the first known case this year of piracy against boat 
people off malaysias coast 
the un statement faxed to the associated press said that of 
the 191 boat people only 171 escaped they had left camau in the 
southern tip of vietnam on april 1 and were attacked the following 
day the statement said 
those who escaped reached an american exxon oil rig off the 
trengganu coast in the south china sea on april 3 the un agency 
said 
they were in a refugee camp awaiting resettlement 
the statement did not identify the pirates but officials said 
information given by the refugees identified the attackers as thai 
fishermen 
the incident underlines once again the importance of granting 
safe haven as soon as possible to vietnamese asylum seekers in 
accord with all humanitarian and maritime obligations the un 
high commissioner said in its statement 
according to the account provided by the un group the pirates 
were in four boats one pulled up alongside the vietnamese vessel 
and offered the refugees ice and water the other boats then 
approached from different directions and surrounded the targeted 
vessel 
three men armed with knives boarded and took watches jewelry 
money and the boats compass they attempted to abduct a 
20yearold female when she resisted one of them stabbed her to 
death and threw her body into the sea 
at that point six or seven men with knives iron rods and 
hacksaws boarded the vietnamese boat and began looting it they 
threw all the food overboard took the battery and most of the 
fuel then abducted six women and left 
one boat later returned and rammed the vietnamese boat at full 
speed causing 20 to 30 people to fall overboard at least two 
vietnamese were stabbed to death when they attempted to grab on the 
ropes hanging down from the pirates boat 
the survivors managed to start up their battered boat again and 
steered it in the direction of the oil platform which could be 
seen in the distance 
the last major piracy attack on the boat people off the 
malaysian coast occured in august 1989 seventyone people drowned 
when pirates looted and sank their boat thirteen survivors were 
picked up by exxon boats 
