<TEXT>
in one vision of 21stcentury detroit people 
would be able to ride cable cars across the detroit river to 
windsor ontario or stroll to work through enclosed skywalks 
the plan unveiled wednesday would turn empty shops to fancy 
apartments extend an elevated rail system and reclaim blighted 
neighborhoods 
weve got a lot of lofty ideas in there but how you carry 
them out is another question said city planner harold smith 
mayor coleman a youngs planning department and the city 
planning commission have traded drafts on a master plan since 1973 
only agreeing on the latest 
the plan would relocate residents of largely abandoned 
neighborhoods and raze buildings so the land could be offered to 
developers it also calls for creating jobs by helping steel 
industries and reestablishing detroit as a recording industry 
center 
planners also envision a fashion district much like new yorks 
seventh avenue along detroits seven mile road reviving of a 
former avenue of fashion 
smith said most of the ideas depend on finding developers and 
money 
