agreement for direct flights of jewish refugees to israel provided 
israel gave assurances they would not be settled in the occupied 
territories 
on thursday night a soviet official specified that means east 
jerusalem as well as the west bank and gaza 
shevardnadze also held out the prospect of resuming normal 
diplomatic ties with israel after a 23year lapse depending on 
the overall middle east situation 
the soviets have consistently demanded that israel hold 
negotiations to create a palestinian state and relinquish all the 
land the arabs lost in the 1967 sixday war that would include the 
west bank gaza east jerusalem and the golan heights 
shevardnadzes white house session with bush ran twice as long 
as initially planned this talk was not only rather lengthy but 
also rather substantive shevardnadze said 
baker said earlier that shevardnadze had not agreed to the 
proposal for direct emigre flights to israel but the soviet 
official did say that they would be willing to give it some 
consideration baker said 
on the subject of german reunification baker said he believes 
the soviets have concluded that a neutral country is not the best 
route to go 
a unified germany as part of nato presented a problem to 
them said baker who has been meeting with his soviet 
counterpart since wednesday 
we were equally firm in our view that the unified germany must 
remain a member of nato and that that would indeed provide 
stability which is after all one of the major results that we 
all seek from the unification of germany baker said 
west german foreign minister hansdietrich genscher has proposed 
keeping nato troops from entering what is now east germany even 
though the merged country is part of the western alliance 
genscher told reporters after an address to the american society 
of newspaper editors what i have heard so far confirms the 
impression of my talks with foreign minister shevardnadze in 
windhoek namely that the soviet union is taking a constructive 
position or attitude both toward the building of a future europe 
and also to german unification which they view as a 
lawabiding process genscher and sheverdnadaze met in windhoek 
namibia last month 
despite some tough soviet actions in the baltics bush on 
thursday scheduled his second summit with gorbachev for may 30 to 
june 3 fitzwater said the president would express his concerns 
forcefully and directly to the soviet leader 
baker said shevardnadze has been consistent throughout the talks 
in declaring that the preferred soviet approach to the independence 
crisis in lithuania is dialogue and that they would like to see 
this resolved through peaceful means and that they rejected the 
concept of use of force 
