a cargo plane apparently lost an 
engine and crashed into the sea killing its american pilot police 
said friday the two other people on the plane were rescued 
the accident occurred thursday evening shortly after the super 
constellation ld49 left san juans international airport for the 
dominican republic police said 
witnesses told local radio station radio reloj they saw one of 
the engines fall the other burst into flames and there was an 
explosion seconds later the witnesses said the plane then plunged 
into the sea near levittown a suburb about 10 miles west of san 
juan 
three police helicopters hovered over the crash scene as police 
marine units and us coast guard and civil defense personnel 
worked to recover the pilots body 
the pilot identified as william bailes apparently drowned 
after being knocked unconscious in the crash police said 
police spokesman baltasar vazquez said bailes was an american 
citizen who lived in the dominican republic 
the two crewmembers aboard the aircraft were identified by 
police as ramon castro lara the flight engineer and miguel de los 
santos both are from the dominican republic police said 
the two jumped out of the plane before it hit the water 
according to the englishlanguage newspaper the san juan star 
which quoted eyewitnesses 
castro lara and de los santos were treated for minor injuries 
police said 
