<TEXT>
latvias communist party met friday to discuss 
whether to follow its baltic neighbors and declare itself 
independent from the soviet communist party news reports said 
about 800 delegates representing latvias 177000 communists 
began a twoday meeting in the capital riga 
the communist parties of neighboring lithuania and estonia have 
already split with moscow and declared their support for 
independence in those republics 
the three balitc republics were forceably annexed by the soviet 
union in 1940 lithuanias legislature declared the republic 
independent march 11 
the kremlin responded by saying the move was illegal and invalid 
and launched a show of force that included sending troops to occupy 
party and government buildings 
the official soviet news agency tass said some latvian 
