<TEXT>
for 50 years university of mississippi 
students who wanted to be editor of the campus newspaper had to be 
elected a procedure critics said picked the best politician not 
the best journalist 
following a spring protest that included publishing blank pages 
in the newspaper the process has been changed 
the next editor of the daily mississippian will be chosen by a 
selection committee instead of elected by the entire student body 
ending a campaign process in which candidates often spent hundreds 
of dollars on posters and fliers 
last month the student government voted 2921 after much debate 
to do away with elections and empower an 11member selection 
committee of faculty and students 
critics said fraternities and sororities controlled the annual 
elections and the votes were little more than popularity contests 
our image is that we are the greek white supremacists who 
dont want the state to be a good place to live for anyone but 
