nasa on friday cleaned discoverys 
engines and replaced a tv camera lens from the shuttle in 
preparation for next weeks mission to launch the 15 billion 
hubble space telescope 
the camera was removed from the shuttles robot arm after 
technicians found the spot on the lens said nasa spokesman bruce 
buckingham 
its not going to impact the schedule at all he said 
mission specialist steven a hawley will use the 50footlong 
arm to deploy the telescope during the fiveday mission a spot on 
the television camera lens might have hampered his view 
the launch countdown was to begin soon after hawley and the four 
other crew members arrived on saturday afternoon 
the shuttle is scheduled to blast off at 847 am tuesday 
things are coming on us in a rush right now said bill 
