to think that in a couple of days well be closing the payload 
doors and it will be the last time well see it until its in 
orbit 
tuesdays launch date was jeopardized earlier this week when a 
power outage interrupted testing of the telescope and orbiter the 
tests were completed thursday eliminating the last major prelaunch 
hurdle 
technicians on friday continued cleaning the shuttles rear 
engine compartment removing protective covers for flight and 
installing essential lastminute items 
