problem was disconnecting the telescopes nickelhydrogen battery 
chargers and removing the instruments dust and moisture 
protection the operation which nasa calls a payload closeout 
was expected to the completed by sunday 
once they get in to disconnecting the umbilicals thats when 
you get into the real serious hubble space telescope closeout 
diller said 
the telescope is the most expensive unmanned spacecraft ever 
built by nasa 
hawley said he has practiced deploying the telescope dozens of 
times and is prepared for just about anything that might go wrong 
im confident we can do it under almost any circumstance he 
said nasas real good at whatifs and weve done a lot 
whatifs what if this part doesnt work what if the arm fails 
completely 
once deployed the telescope is to orbit 380 miles high for 15 
years enabling astronomers to study stars and galaxies so distant 
that their light has been traveling to earth for 14 billion years 
it will be capable of detecting objects 50 times fainter and 
with 10 times greater clarity than the best groundbased 
observatory 
