<TEXT>
parliament voted friday to eliminate the 
dreaded sb secret police the old uniformed interior ministry and 
the citizens militia in a dramatic assertion of civilian control 
by the solidarityled government 
the interior ministry is to become a smaller civilianrun 
office it had been staffed by uniformed functionaries along 
military lines and was considered part of the national defense 
system 
the new ministry will oversee the newly created police and 
office of state protection firefighters and a border guard that 
will be separated from the army 
members of the citizens militia the paramilitary force 
previously charged with fighting crime and enforcing the law can 
automatically become police officers similar to those in western 
countries 
secret police officers hired before august 1989 when poland got 
its first noncommunist prime minister in four decades will be 
dismissed only those officers who pass a review process proving 
they are innocent of past abuses will be rehired into the new 
smaller office of state protection 
the sb monitored and harassed dissidents and even ordinary 
citizens to maintain the communist partys grip on power in poland 
the office of state protection is to limit its activities to 
fighting espionage and authentic threats to national security 
the changes were adopted in three separate bills 
sb officers murdered the prosolidarity priest the rev jerzy 
popieluszko in 1984 and were suspected in scores of political 
killings a parliamentary commission is working to uncover past sb 
abuses 
as a safeguard the new interior ministry is to include a 
civilian advisory commission 
local governments for the first time will be permitted to 
establish their own police force 
the secret police force was pared from 24000 officers last june 
to 3100 this year the government has said some reportedly took 
early retirement and some were permitted to transfer to the 
citizens militia after retraining 
the citizens militia has an estimated 80000 officers 
nationwide 
