escobars hometown is under martial law and the army colonel in 
charge is empowered to arrest any official who tries to impede 
investigations of the local police force known as the department 
of security and control 
after the army took over people started making their way to 
brigade headquarters to report the killings of family members 
lately police had begun killing wealthy townspeople who somehow 
angered the drug traffickers residents said in the beginning the 
department of security and control had concentrated on cleaning 
envigados streets of beggars thieves and people who smoked 
basuko a cocaine base 
they focused on murdering and torturing street people 
miguel moreno unemployed told the associated press two days after 
the police force was disbanded they took me into the 
headquarters and beat me up many times just because my clothes were 
dirty 
during the interview moreno waved cars into parking spaces next 
to envigados main plaza and tried to hustle the drivers for change 
army motorcycle patrols rumbled past the white church that 
towers over the plaza 
i would rather have a million soldiers in this town than those 
damn security agents said leo gomez also unemployed 
sergio jesus jimenez 23 sat in his wheelchair at a sidewalk 
cafe and told how the police shot him in the back eight months 
earlier crippling him for life 
jimenez said he and some friends were watching a soccer game on 
a storewindow television when a police patrol four men and a 
woman came around the corner 
when we saw them we began to run he said thats when 
they shot me they put me in the hospital for six days and then 
threw me in jail even though i couldnt walk 
he said police released him when they found he had no record 
jimenez an orphan who lives with his four brothers in the poor 
sebastiana neighborhood admitted to smoking basuko from time to 
time 
the same traffickers who export tons of cocaine to the united 
states and other countries dont want to see a poor person even 
thinking about smoking basuko on the street in envigado he said 
envigado appears to have fewer homeless people than other 
colombian towns although residents call it the nations monaco 
however the business district remains a typical crowded jumble of 
shops and restaurants 
most of the money escobar put into his birthplace seems to have 
financed condominium construction in wealthy neighborhoods 
it is said the drug traffickers have invested in envigado and 
made life better for the people here but at the same time they 
send the police out to kill the poorest jimenez said i was in 
the army and even in the army we didnt shoot people for no 
reason 
octavio arturo gonzalito william jairo the young man 
said reciting a litany of names of friends he said were victims of 
the police 
edwin arredondo galvis a 15yearold half brother said bodies 
would show up under a bridge leading to their neighborhood i 
would see six or seven at a time he said 
mayorelect jose mario rodriguez said the army had overreacted 
we cannot see the justification of the military presence but 
we will cooperate with the officials he said 
rodriguez takes office aug 1 but will have no power if martial 
law still is in effect 
the mayorelect said he was certain the army would realize 
envigado was a peaceful place and leave soon 
we continue in peace as we always have he said we invite 
people to come and see how tranquil life here really is 
jimenez in his wheelchair said silence does not necessarily 
mean peace he said families of victims had been afraid to speak up 
about police links to the drug cartel but now that the killers 
are in jail people are getting up the courage to talk 
he would go to army headquarters himself to report his injury if 
he had the money for a taxi but how am i suppose to get to the 
brigade in this jimenez said pointing to his wheelchair 
a former city policeman who would identify himself only as 
freddy said envigado had no problems except crimes committed by 
people like jimenez who smoked basuko 
the department has done a good job here said the officer 
who was playing cards with several men in a cafe in 1989 we 
detained 900 people the national police didnt take in 5 percent 
of that figure 
freddy weighs about 120 pounds has a thin face and shows 
rotting teeth when he smiles his friends called him freddy the 
mouse 
rodriguez the mayorelect said envigados problems had been 
blown out of proportion 
i think people are exaggerating because they envy envigados 
wealth and its excellent administration he said and declared 
his municipality to be the only one in colombia with unemployment 
benefits 
a high tax base and such thriving industries as textiles and 
chemicals paid for that not money from cocaine traffickers he 
said 
people associate the town with pablo escobar because he was 
born here but i for one have never met the man rodriguez said 
freddy the mouse predicted the department of security and 
control would be back in business soon 
the government needs us he said they just dont realize 
how badly 
