<TEXT>
the agency that regulates the futures markets 
is moving closer to correcting problems uncovered in the scandals 
on the chicago exchanges 
the commodity futures trading commission voted unanimously 
thursday to submit for public comment a proposed rule that would 
provide a legal definition of broker associations and require them 
to register with the exchange at which they do business 
broker associations have been loosely defined as formal or 
informal groups of futures traders formed to provide more capital 
to finance trades and more people to handle them 
but the cftcs division of trading and markets concluded in a 
study reported on last january that broker associations may 
increase the potential for certain types of trading abuses 
the study was an outgrowth of last years undercover 
investigation of trading at the chicago board of trade and the 
chicago mercantile exchange the nations two largest futures 
exchanges which resulted in the indictment of more than 40 
traders 
only five of the 13 futures exchanges have rules defining broker 
associations of those only the chicago mercantile exchange new 
yorks commodity exchange and the coffee sugar amp cocoa exchange 
require broker associations to register 
cftc staffers believe that keeping tabs on broker associations 
will help deter abuses in the trading pits commission members 
agreed by a 50 vote 
i believe very strongly that we identify and register these 
groups and i also agree that it gives a big assist and augmentation 
to our surveillance program to have this information said 
commissioner kalo a hineman 
as defined in the cftcs proposed rules broker association 
refers to two or more exchange members who share responsibility for 
executing customer orders profits or losses from trading 
activities or access to each others unfilled customer orders 
the rule would bar participation in the trading activities of a 
broker association unless the association is registered with the 
market or exchange 
interested parties have 60 days to comment on the proposed rule 
before the cftc takes a final vote on it 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

