designed to be less harmful to the environment than existing grades 
phillips reformulated fuel blended to reduce certain 
hydrocarbon emissions will be tested in st louis one of more 
than 100 cities that fall below the environmental protection 
agencys minimum standards for air quality the company said 
thursday 
the rush by americas oil companies to make gasoline less toxic 
comes in response to stepped up government efforts to reduce air 
emissions from the tailpipes of cars and trucks 
george gaspar a stock analyst for robert w baird amp co in 
milwaukee said oil companies are trying to protect their markets 
by developing cleaner gasoline that will help auto companies 
meet tougher air emission standards 
if the auto companies dont get any help they may have to take 
some major actions that could hurt the petroleum industry said 
gaspar were going to hear a lot about how great reformulated 
gasoline is 
phillips based in bartlesville okla sells gasoline in the 
midwest it selected st louis for the test because of the 
companys strong selling base in the area 
the reformulated gasoline is blended to reduce the amounts of 
certain hydrocarbons such as aromatics benzene and olefins that 
react with the atmosphere and produce ozone a main component of 
smog 
charles bowerman a phillips senior vice president said the 
midgrade gasoline superclean unleaded plus contains 20 to 30 
percent less olefins and aromatics and 35 percent less benzene than 
the average gasoline sold in the st louis area the company did 
not make a comparison with the average gasoline sold nationally 
the new gasoline is made by removing the more toxic compounds 
and replacing them with methyltertiarybutylether a blending 
component with a high oxygen content 
other oil companies that have introduced reformulated gasolines 
include arco marathon exxon amoco mobil citgo and sun oil 
while the new gasolines are slightly better for the environment 
theyre only a small step in attempts to end smog and other 
pollution in americas cities said scott denman director of the 
safe energy communication council 
theyre missing the forest for the trees said denman 
these new gasolines are a little more benign on the environment 
but they are not the best way for us to reduce pollution 
the safe energy communication council based in washington is a 
national coalition of environmental groups working to promote 
alternate energy sources and better use of current ones 
denman said that while phillips and other of the nations oil 
companies tout their efforts to devise environmentally improved 
gasoline theyre also fighting tooth and nail against 
establishing higher fuel efficiency standards 
making cars more fuel efficient and reducing the amount of 
gasoline burned in engines is the best way to clean up the 
environment denman said 
auto companies could use more efficient fuelinjection systems 
build lighter motors design more aerodynamic bodies use lighter 
materials and equip cars with fuelsmart tires that deflate and 
inflate to improve gas mileage he said 
im not saying we shouldnt improve the gasoline but i think 
we should recognize it for what it is a small step and ask why 
were not taking some of the much bigger steps denman said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

