<TEXT>
importer ronald v davis has adopted the market 
revival of perrier sparkling water as a personal mission 
i feel like my family has been attacked said the 
43yearold father of two teenagers in describing his emotional 
reaction to the worst problem hes faced in two decades in the 
beverage business 
davis president and chief executive of perrier group of america 
inc in greenwich conn felt a misstep in handling perriers 
contamination crisis could damage the french brands image for 
decades 
but he relied on instinct and the advice of longtime colleagues 
in ordering the recall feb 9 of every perrier bottle in the united 
states the government had alerted the company that several bottles 
of perrier in north carolina were found to have trace amounts of 
benzene a dangerous chemical 
you cant be trained for an event like this he said 
when specially marked perrier is returned to american stores 
bars and restaurants in a few weeks davis hopes customers will 
respond by restoring perrier to its former stature as the nations 
bestselling imported water 
the big red flag that seemed about to go up and wave and kill 
the cachet of the brand never went up and davis is responsible for 
that said tom pirko president of the beverage consultant 
bevmark inc of los angeles 
pirko initially expected perriers share of the 22 billion 
us bottled water market would drop 10 to 15 percent in the 
aftermath of the contamination and recall but he says now the 
damage is going to be very minor and pentup demand could make 
the brand stronger than ever 
critics said davis was not quick enough in explaining to 
consumers directly through advertising rather than through news 
media briefings how the perrier bottles became contaminated a 
halfdozen lawsuits have been filed against the company alleging 
that the product has been misrepresented as pure 
davis said the company acted responsibly in reaction to the 
crisis and that the lawsuits are groundless he said he ordered the 
recall voluntarily after independent laboratory analyses indicated 
the contamination was not confined to a single batch of perrier or 
a single part of the country 
source perrier sa the french bottler which owns 53 percent of 
privately held perrier group initially blamed a workers improper 
use of a cleaning solvent containing benzene for the contamination 
but the contamination was later traced to the gas reservoir that 
lies beneath the spring from which perrier is drawn in vergezes 
while the water was pure source perrier discovered benzene occurs 
in small amounts in the gas and a filter failed to screen it out 
before bottling 
the company said it took steps to monitor and replace filters 
more often so the contamination will not happen again 
in a recent interview davis was unable to cite anything in his 
professional career that includes nearly 10 years in general foods 
beverage division that compared with the stresses of the 
contamination incident 
davis lives with his wife son and daughter in greenwich an 
affluent new york suburb he was born jan 26 1947 and grew up 
near los angeles where a dispenser of arrowhead bottled water now 
one of perrier groups brands was a fixture in his house 
after college davis joined general foods and worked on the 
country time lemonade brand he moved to perrier group in 1979 
intent on expanding its business which amounted to 20 million in 
annual sales and one brand perrier 
davis became president and chief executive the next year and 
the company has grown to 640 million in annual sales and nine 
brands 
a marathon runner and an avid golfer who regularly shoots in the 
70s davis is described as competitive he hates to lose whether 
we are playing gin rummy or are on the golf course even if its only 
1 at stake said louis a matagrano head of a beverage 
distributorship that has handled perrier for 10 years in san mateo 
county south of san francisco 
davis said he became aware of reports from north carolina that a 
private laboratory had discovered bottles of perrier were 
contaminated on feb 6 the company gets calls 15 to 18 times a 
year from someone saying they have found something that usually 
prove groundless he said 
but over the next three days both the federal government and 
the companys independent tests disclosed trace amounts of benzene 
in perrier bottles selected randomly in various regions 
davis said he was assured the benzene levels posed no safety or 
health hazard and the government was not demanding any action but 
he said it was clear on friday feb 9 what should be done 
after all the products ad theme was its perfect its 
perrier 
kim jeffery the former pepsicola co executive who is davis 
top marketing ally suggested the recall in a conference call that 
friday as he and davis talked to frederik zimmer managing director 
of source perrier in france 
davis said they instantly agreed we could have sat there and 
agonized but that didnt happen it was like all three of us were 
together he said 
he said expense was not an issue reclaiming the 70 million 
bottles cost about 30 million alone when a products whole 
reason for being is quality and purity the costs of not doing what 
we did would have been borne for the next 100 years davis said 
the recall was announced friday afternoon perriers 178 
distributors were told by telephone and fax they were not to load 
the trucks on monday 
on saturday packages were sent to distributors by courier 
telling them to collect all the bottles and outlining reimbursement 
procedures davis held a news conference a tollfree telephone 
line for consumers was activated sunday 
on monday davis went to france where it took three days to 
pinpoint the cause he talked by phone with james burke who guided 
johnson amp johnson through two tylenol poisonings in the 1980s 
burkes advice be straight 
the next week perrier hired bursonmarsteller the 
communications company they worked on the tylenol case by march 6 
the recall was virtually complete and davis announced plans to 
relaunch ther brand by summer 
it ran a fullpage ad in 22 major newspapers admitting a 
mistake that it said was identified and corrected 
bevmarks pirko said perrier evidently will not suffer from the 
disclosure that benzene is present in the gas reservoir used to 
make the water fizzy the harpoon that could have stuck went 
whizzing by he said 
industry executives applaud davis i have enormous respect for 
what he did considering what little he knew about it when he made 
his decision said jack west owner of puro corp a water 
company serving offices in metropolitan new york 
