champion spark plug co said friday it would 
consolidate its us operations by closing two plants because of 
less demand for spark plugs 
the move will affect 675 salaried and hourly workers 245 in 
detroit and 430 in toledo 
the two plants will be phased out over the next two years 
production will be integrated into the companys burlington iowa 
and cambridge ohio operations champion employs 10000 people 
worldwide 
judging from the factors that exist today its not only 
inevitable its the right thing to do william basedow director 
of employee relations said at a news conference 
company officials and representatives of the united auto workers 
union are to meet regarding how the timing of the consolidation 
will affect production and maintenance employees 
company officials said new jobs in burlington and cambridge 
would be created 
champion has been struggling for several years with an 
overcapacity of production facilities while at the same time 
selling a product spark plugs whose overall market has 
declined said jerry godwin champion president 
champion plants in toledo produce spark plug shells and assemble 
the final spark plugs the detroit plant manufactures ceramic 
insulation used in the plug 
champion is a division of houstonbased cooper industries inc 
which bought the company last year for 707 million 
basedow said champions plans have nothing to do with the sale 
saying the company had to streamline to remain competitive 
the prior management had a similar study and came to much the 
same conclusions that we have had these factors been in place 
in 1988 1989 they would have done the same thing he said 
basedow said the declining spark plug market was caused by a 
reduction in the number of cylinders in automobiles because of 
smaller engines improvements in the ignition systems on most 
vehicles and in the spark plugs themselves resulting in longer 
life and unleaded fuel which does not damage spark plugs as does 
leaded fuel 
foreign spark plugs entering the country as original equipment 
in imported cars also contributed to falling demand 
