sentencing for june 18 and teichers for june 19 
testifying for the prosecution were two key government witnesses 
who pled guilty to insider trading charges in 1986 michael david 
worked as an attorney in the corporate department of the top new 
york law firm paul weiss rifkind wharton amp garrison where he 
gathered information on clients and passed it along to the 
defendants 
also testifying against the pair was robert salsbury who worked 
with frankel in drexels arbitrage department 
