<TEXT>
the widow of a businessman who killed himself 
so his insurance money could finance a battle with the internal 
revenue service pleaded with congress friday to control the irs 
to keep it from destroying peoples lives 
this kind of thing should never have happened to me and 
alex kay m council of high point nc told the senate finance 
oversight subcommittee we didnt do anything wrong we just got 
caught up in the middle of a big irs screwup and we couldnt get 
out of it 
irs commissioner fred t goldberg jr who preceded mrs council 
on the witness stand was not asked about her case but said his 
agency in general is making a great deal of progress implementing 
the 1988 law known as the taxpayer bill of rights 
citizens of this country have more rights today in proceeding 
against the irs than against any other agency and i think that 
is good goldberg said he said employees have been put on notice 
that we need to be attentive to attitudes 
nine years after the councils got into trouble with the irs by 
