lotus development corp and novell inc agreed to 
merge their computer software companies friday a move that could 
give lotus a leading edge in the software industry 
the companies signed a letter of intent under which novell would 
become a subsidiary of lotus after the stockswap merger no cash 
would change hands 
the primary reason for the merger is we were two companies 
both leading in our prospective markets and we figured we could do 
better things for our customers if we got together said jim 
manzi chairman chief executive officer and president of lotus 
were sort of perfectly complementary 
the agreement is subject to the approval of the boards of 
directors and stockholders of both companies in addition to 
standard regulatory approvals the companies said the merger is 
expected to be completed by july 
under the agreement lotus would swap 191931 shares of lotus 
common stock for each share of novell common stock lotus would 
issue about 416 million new shares to carry out the transaction 
novell was worth a total of about 13 billion at end of trading 
friday while lotus was worth 15 billion making the merger worth 
28 billion said david bayer an analyst at montgomery securities 
in san francisco 
