<TEXT>
general electric co has filed a 115 
billion lawsuit against daimlerbenz of west germany claiming that 
daimlers new alliance with united technologies corp breached an 
agreement it already had with ge to develop jet engines 
the suit was filed tuesday in us district court in new york 
just one week after daimlerbenz announced it had signed a 
preliminary agreement with utc to allow their jet engine divisions 
to operate as a single company on certain ventures 
ge claims that daimlerbenz because of its strengthened ties 
to utcs pratt amp whitney division could give away ges jet engine 
trade secrets to utc 
pratt amp whitney and ge are fierce competitors in the jet engine 
business 
a utc spokesman on friday dismissed assertions that ge trade 
secrets were jeopardized by the collaboration between daimlers jet 
engine division motorenund turbinenunion and pratt amp whitney 
neither utc nor pratt amp whitney needs wants or would accept 
confidential ge information said utc spokesman dan harrison 
we have complete confidence in the integrity of daimlerbenz mtu 
and its people 
daimlerbenz an aerospace electronics and auto giant said it 
was studying the suit but at this time saw no grounds for the 
action 
the lawsuit alleges that ge claims that daimlerbenz and its jet 
engine division already had a series of binding agreements to work 
exclusively with ge in developing a new generation of highthrust 
commercial jet engines 
the suit seeks damages of 115 billion and court injunctions to 
bar daimlerbenz from using trade secrets or working with any 
company including utc and pratt amp whitney to develop jet 
engines that compete directly with engines covered under 
gedaimlerbenz agreements 
ge refused to comment on specifics in the lawsuit or on its 
longstanding business relationship with the daimlerbenz jet engine 
division 
