for itself ge spokesman george jamison said friday 
harrison defended the new agreement reached between 
hartfordbased utc and daimlerbenz calling it a logical 
outgrowth of a 20year association between the two companies 
mtu is now participating in three jet engine programs with pratt 
amp whitney and plans additional partnerships under the new 
alliance although the strengthened relationship is not a merger 
the agreement means the two companies will act as one in designing 
engineering and marketing new engines 
in its suit ge says it has had contracts with mtu for more than 
25 years covering the sharing of confidential technological 
information revenues and costs for the development and sale of 
commercial jet engines 
