<TEXT>
a federal jury on friday awarded about 100 million 
to windmere corp in an antitrust suit charging that the dutch 
company nv philips had monopolized the rotary shaver market 
the verdict came in a counterclaim by windmere against philips 
and its subsidiary north american philips co makers of the 
norelco shaver philips had initially filed suit in the case 
against windmere charging unfair competition 
the jury cleared windmere on that charge accepting the miami 
lakes companys contention that philips had attempted to monopolize 
the market through predatory pricing in violation of the sherman 
act 
were very pleased with the jurys verdict said david 
friedson president and chief executive officer of windmere 
were going to have a good party 
the jury awarded windmere 298 million which is trebled 
automatically under the sherman act to 896 million the jury also 
awarded reasonable attorneys fees interests and costs bringing 
the estimated total to more than 100 million according to 
windmere attorneys 
the rotary shaver war was started by philips in 1984 as part 
of an attempt to drive windmere out of the rotary business said 
gary hoffman an attorney for windmere 
the 87 million verdict gives windmere the funds that it needs 
to reenter the markets and provide effective competition against 
the philips companies 
hoffman said philips controls about 95 percent of the 165 
million rotary shaver market 
windmere attorney gary jones said the appeals process would 
likely hold up payment of the award until mid1991 but he said the 
company is confident the jurys verdict would be upheld 
the case was first filed in washington dc in 1984 and a 
jury found in favor of windmere on the monopolization issue while a 
judge directed a guilty verdict against windmere in the unfair 
competition provision 
the verdicts were overturned on appeal however and retried in 
miami the decision friday capped a fourweek trial before us 
district judge stanley marcus 
hoffman who also represents sears roebuck amp co in a similar 
suit filed by philips said he will ask for a summary judgment 
against philips in that case based on fridays verdict 
windmere employs about 300 people in miami lakes and has 50 to 
100 other employees around the country said friedson the 
companys manufacturing plants are in china and hong kong 
</TEXT>
